remove(int) - Method in class LinkedList
the remove(index) is supposed to remove the node at index it achieves this by first parsing through the list until it reaches the index it will then remove the item and unlink the node from nearby nodes and then it will link those adjacent nodes to each other
remove(int) - Method in interface List
Removes and returns the item at 'index'
remove(Object) - Method in interface Collection
Removes 'item' from this collection, and returns what was removed If 'item' does not exist in this collection, do not modify the collection, and return null Note that you must return the item removed from this collection, not the parameter 'item'
remove(Object) - Method in class LinkedList
the remove(item) is expected to remove an item from the list it achieves this by first looking for the node that conatins the object then based on where the item is located removes it and unlinks it from adjacent nodes
removeFirst() - Method in class LinkedList
Removes and returns the first item from this linked list
removeLast() - Method in class LinkedList
Removes and returns the last item from this linked list
